@20001  = ~Rogue~
@20002  = ~ROGUE: To accomplish <PRO_HISHER> goals, for good or ill, the typical Rogue is a skilled pilferer. Cunning, nimbleness, and stealth are <PRO_HISHER> hallmarks. Whether <PRO_HESHE> turns <PRO_HISHER> talent against innocent passersby and wealthy merchants or oppressors and monsters is a choice for the Rogue to make.

CLASS FEATURES:

- May not wear armor heavier than studded leather.
- May not equip shields larger than bucklers.
- May only use the following weapons: long sword, short sword, katana, scimitar, dagger, club, quarterstaff, crossbow, shortbow, dart, sling.
- May only become Proficient (one slot) in any weapon class.
- May only become Proficient (one slot) in any fighting style.
- May distribute 20 points per level (30 at level 1) in thieving abilities: Open Locks, Pick Pockets, Find Traps, Move Silently, Hide In Shadows, Detect Illusion, Set Traps.
- Starts with base scores of 10% in Open Locks, 5% in Find Traps, 15% in Pick Pockets, 10% in Move Silently, and 5% in Hide in Shadows.
- May backstab for increased damage:
  Level 1-8: x2
  Level 9-17: x3
  Level 18+: x4
- May learn 'Rogue Feats' which provide the rogue with special abilities or passive bonuses. Rogues begin with three Rogue Feats, and may choose another at every odd level, up to level 19.
- Hit Die: d6

ROGUE FEATS: 
- Stealth Mastery
- Thieving Mastery
- Detection Mastery
- Lore Mastery
- Tracking
- Set Dart Trap
- Set Fire Trap
- Basic Alchemy
- Grease Jar/Smoke Bomb
- Flaming Weapon
- Dodge
- Missile Snaring
- Spell Evasion
- Mental Resilience
- Physical Resilience
- Slippery Mind
- Combat Training
- Ranged Accuracy
- Precise Strike
- Weapon Focus
- Enhanced Backstab
- Fighting Dirty
- Blind Opponent
- Disrupt Magic
- Illusion Magic (level 9+)
- Shadow Magic (level 9+)
- Use Magical Device (level 9+)
- Luck Bonus

CLASS RESTRICTIONS:
- Alignment restricted to any except lawful good.

Prime Requisite For Dual-Classing: Dexterity
~
