@20015  = ~FIGHTER: The Fighter is a champion, swords<PRO_MANWOMAN>, soldier, and brawler who lives or dies by <PRO_HISHER> knowledge of weapons and tactics. Fighters can be found at the front of any battle, contesting toe-to-toe with monsters and villains. A good Fighter needs to be strong and healthy if <PRO_HESHE> hopes to survive.

CLASS FEATURES:

- May wear helmets.
- May wear any armor and use any weapon.
- May achieve Grand Mastery (five slots) with any weapon class.
- May achieve Specialization (two slots) in any fighting style and allocate three slots in Two-Weapon Style.
- May learn 'Warrior Feats' which provide the Fighter with special abilities or passive bonuses. Fighters may choose a feat at every third level, up to level 18.
- Hit Die: d10

WARRIOR FEATS: 
- Health Conditioning
- Toughness
- Intestinal Fortitude
- Unflagging Determination
- Mental Resilience
- Physical Resilience
- Dodge
- Combat Training
- Ranged Accuracy
- Precise Strike
- Group Tactics: Discipline
- Group Tactics: Formation
- Fighting Posture: Aggressive
- Fighting Posture: Disarming
- Fighting Posture: Parry Slashing
- Fighting Posture: Parry Piercing
- Fighting Posture: Parry Blunt

Prime Requisites For Dual-Classing: Strength~
@20016  = ~RANGER: The Ranger is a warrior and a woods<PRO_MANWOMAN> who is skilled with weapons and is knowledgeable in the ways of the forest. The Ranger often protects and guides lost travelers and honest peasant-folk. A Ranger needs to be strong and wise to the ways of nature to live a full life.

CLASS FEATURES:

- May wear helmets.
- May wear any armor and use any weapon.
- May not exceed Specialization (two slots) in any weapon class.
- May achieve Specialization (two slots) in any fighting style.
- Begins Specialized (two slots) in Two-Weapon Style and may place a third slot into it. 
- May select a racial enemy, which grants a +4 bonus to hit and damage rolls against the selected enemy race.
- May use the Charm Animal ability once per day. Gains one use at level 1 and an additional use every 2 levels thereafter.
- May use the Hide In Shadows ability while wearing no armor, leather armor, or studded leather armor.
- May cast druidic spells starting at level 8.
- Alignment restricted to good.
- May learn 'Warrior Feats' which provide special abilities or passive bonuses. Rangers may choose a feat at every third level, up to level 18.
- Hit Die: d10

RANGER FEATS: 
- Tracking
- Quickstride
- Health Conditioning
- Toughness
- Intestinal Fortitude
- Unflagging Determination
- Mental Resilience
- Physical Resilience
- Dodge
- Combat Training
- Weapon Focus
- Ranged Accuracy
- Precise Strike
- Enhanced Backstab
- Fighting Posture: Aggressive
- Fighting Posture: Disarming
- Fighting Posture: Parry Slashing
- Fighting Posture: Parry Piercing
- Fighting Posture: Parry Blunt

Prime Requisites For Dual-Classing: Strength, Dexterity, Wisdom~
@20017  = ~BARBARIAN: A Barbarian can be an excellent warrior. While not as disciplined or as skilled as a Fighter, the Barbarian can willingly throw <PRO_HIMHER>self into a berserker rage, becoming a tougher and stronger opponent.

CLASS FEATURES:

- May not wear armor heavier than splint mail.
- May not exceed Specialization (two slots) with any weapon class.
- May achieve Specialization (two slots) in any fighting style and allocate three slots in Two-Weapon Style.
- May learn 'Warrior Feats' which provide special abilities or passive bonuses. Barbarians may choose a feat at every third level, up to level 18.
- Moves 2 points faster than other characters.
- Immune to backstab.
- Gains an extra chance to roll a saving throw to resist spells and abilities that involve Sleep, Hold, Charm, Domination, Confusion, Feeblemind, Stun, and Maze effects.
- May use the Rage ability once per day. Gains one use at level 1 and an additional use every 4 levels thereafter.

RAGE: The enraged status lasts for 5 rounds and provides a +4 bonus to Strength and Constitution, a -2 penalty to Armor Class and a +2 bonus to Saving Throws vs. Spell, as well as immunity to all panic and fear effects.

- 11th level: Gains 10% resistance to crushing, slashing, piercing, and missile damage.
- Hit Die: d12

BARBARIAN FEATS: 
- Tracking
- Health Conditioning
- Toughness
- Intestinal Fortitude
- Mental Resilience
- Physical Resilience
- Dodge
- Combat Training
- Ranged Accuracy
- Fighting Posture: Aggressive
~
@20018  = ~Barbarian Rage
The character is enraged for 5 rounds, which grants <PRO_HIMHER> a +4 bonus to Strength and Constitution, a -2 penalty to Armor Class, and a +2 bonus to Saving Throws vs. Spell, as well as immunity to all panic and fear effects.~
@20073  = ~ASSASSIN: This is a killer trained in discreet and efficient murder, relying on anonymity and surprise to perform <PRO_HISHER> task.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: Stealth Bonus, THAC0 Bonus, and Melee Trick: Blind Opponent.
- May learn the Backstab Bonus feat up to three times, reaching a possible maximum multiplier of x7.
- May learn two special Assassin-only feats: Poison Weapon (Toxin) and Poison Trap.
~
@20074  = ~HUNTER: This rogue is skilled in tracking and capturing quarry - both beasts, and humanoids. Hunters are specially trained at their task and make fearsome opponents. They have honed their trap-making abilities well beyond that of the average rogue.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: Detection Bonus, Dart Trap, and Basic Alchemy
- May learn two special feats unique to Hunters: Poison Weapon (Paralytic) and Web Trap.
~
@20075  = ~hunter~
@20076  = ~Hunter~
@20077  = ~SWASHBUCKLER: This rogue is part acrobat, part swords<PRO_MANWOMAN>, and part wit: the epitome of charm and grace.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: AC Bonus, THAC0 Bonus, and Precise Strike (+5% crit chance).
- May repeat learning the AC Bonus and THAC0 Bonus feats, up to four times each.
- May learn two special feats: Swashbuckling and Escape Artist. Swashbuckling is a temporary ability that the Swashbuckler more annoying and harder to hit in melee combat. Escape Artist allows the Swashbuckler a chance to escape whenever Held, Webbed, or otherwise helpless.
- May Specialize (two slots) in any melee weapon available to Thieves.
- May place 3 slots into Two-Weapon Style.

Disadvantages:
- Swashbucklers have no backstab multipliers by default; they may raise it to a maximum of x2 by choosing the Backstab Bonus feat.
- May not learn any trap-setting feats.
~
@20078  = ~SHADOWDANCER: Shadowdancers can harness the power of shadow magic to increase their stealth abilities. Enigmatic and dangerous, these uniquely skilled rogues are able to blend seamlessly into the shadows in ways that a normal thief cannot, striking without warningâ€”sometimes with supernatural speed.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: Stealth Bonus, Smoke Bomb, Grease Jar, and Saving Throws Bonus.
- May learn the Shadow Magic feat up to 5 times. This magical ability can mimic one of the following spells: Sanctuary, Blindness, Shadow Door, Shadowstep, or Summon Shadow.

Disadvantages:
- Alignment restricted to any non-lawful.
- -1 to base backstab multiplier compared to an unkitted Thief

Prime Requisites For Dual-Classing: Strength, Dexterity, Charisma~
@20081   = ~alchemist~
@20082   = ~Alchemist~
@20083   = ~ALCHEMIST: This is someone who focuses on pursuits of the mind more than of the body, achieving mastery over herbs and chemicals. Alchemists may learn to brew more, and more useful, potions than most rogues, and may even use their knowledge to alter their own physiology.

Abilities:
- Begins with the following rogue feats at 1st level: Basic Alchemy, Flaming Weapon, and Grease Jar/Smoke Bomb.
- May learn to use the poisons of the Assassin and the Hunter.
- May learn the Basic Alchemy feat a 2nd time, resulting in the ability to create two potions per day.  After learning Basic Alchemy twice, two new feats become available:
- Advanced Alchemy, which allows for the creation of more powerful and tactically useful potions.
- Hulking Transformation, which allows the Alchemist to temporarily turn into a powerful brute, at a cost to <PRO_HISHER> own Strength and Constitution.
- While most rogues may choose the Advanced Alchemy feat as an HLA, Alchemists may choose a more powerful version: High-Level Alchemy.

ADVANCED ALCHEMY: this ability allows the Alchemist to craft one of the following potion once per day: a Potion of Regeneration; an Oil of Speed; a Potion of Clarity; a Potion of Mind Focusing; a Potion of Invisibility; or a Potion of Fiery Burning.

Restrictions:
- Alchemists have no backstab multiplier by default, and may not raise it via feats.
- May not learn any combat feats.
~
