@4206  = ~swashbuckler~
@4207  = ~Swashbuckler~
@4208  = ~SWASHBUCKLER: This rogue is part acrobat, part duellist, and part wit: the epitome of charm and grace. Swashbucklers are seen by many as dandies, and they generally make poor thieves. But their skill with blades is not to be underestimated; it usually gets them out of trouble when charm fails.

Abilities:
- +1 bonus to Armor Class and thac0 at 1st level, plus an additional +1 bonus every 6 levels.
- May achieve High Mastery (++++) in light bladed weapons (long sword, scimitar, short sword, dagger, darts).
- Begins with one proficiency point in Single-Weapon Style, and may add one more.
- Begins with one proficiency point in Two-Weapon Style, and may add two more.
- Can use use the Swashbuckling skill.  While Swashbuckling, the character wheels and spins and parries, gaining a 2-point bonus to Armor Class against melee attacks and a 1-point penalty to damage and to-hit rolls.  Further, strikes against enemies can cause the target to miss more often.
- Swashbucklers have a +1 bonus to saves vs. Breath for each 5 levels of experience.

Restrictions:
- May not use traps.
- May only distribute 15 skill points per level among thieving skills.
- The swashbuckler can backstab, but with reduced power.
- May not dual-class to fighter.
~
